HEADWORD: Superfluitant
<hw>Su`per*flu"i*tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>super</ets> above + <ets>fluitans</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>fluitare</ets> intensive fr. <ets>fluere</ets> to flow.]</ety>
<def>Floating above or on the surface.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Sir
T. Browne.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Su`per*flu"i*tance</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
